        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 12:45PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wolfe City, or 11 miles north of Commerce, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Roxton around 110 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Noble, Allens Point,
Dial, Forest Hill, Bug Tussle, Ladonia, Petty, Fairlie, Ben Franklin,
and Pecan Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
